DESIGN INSPIRATION & PATTERN ATTRIBUTION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

calm-design's reference patterns, anti-slop blocklist, dial parameters, and
9-section DESIGN.md format draw inspiration from the following open-source
design skill projects. While calm-design's implementations are written
independently and extended for Korean-first environments, the conceptual
foundations are explicitly attributed below.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7. awesome-design-md
   Source:    https://github.com/VoltAgent/awesome-design-md
   License:   MIT
   Influence: 9-section DESIGN.md format originator. calm-design uses this
              standard with adaptations (Section 7 'Motion' replaces 'Do's/Don'ts',
              Section 9 'Anti-Patterns' replaces 'Agent Prompt Guide').
              The reference-library/global/ directory imports 69 brand
              DESIGN.md entries from this project (see Phase 3 README).

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
8. taste-skill
   Source:    https://github.com/Leonxlnx/taste-skill
   License:   Public use (no formal license file)
   Influence: Anti-slop philosophy, 3-dial parameter system (extended to 4 in
              calm-design with LANGUAGE), Pre-Flight Checklist concept, and
              Creative Arsenal pattern catalog. calm-design's 50-item
              ai-tells-blocklist, 30-item Pre-Flight, and 50+ Creative Arsenal
              expand on taste-skill's foundations.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
9. stitch-skills
   Source:    https://github.com/google-labs-code/stitch-skills
   Copyright: Google Labs and contributors
   License:   Apache License, Version 2.0
   Influence: Prompt enhancement 4-technique pipeline, design-md analysis
              workflow, taste-design anti-slop principles, and workflow
              routing patterns. calm-design's prompt-enhancement.md adapts
              these techniques with Korean keyword mappings.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
10. supanova-design-skill
    Source:    https://github.com/uxjoseph/supanova-design-skill
    License:   Public use (no formal license file)
    Influence: Korean typography enforcement (Pretendard mandatory,
               word-break: keep-all), single-accent color policy, and the
               $150k-agency quality bar. calm-design's typography-ko.md
               extends supanova's policy with deeper line-height/tracking/
               weight rules grounded in Korean SaaS observation.

